    refactor unary expression generation (#190)

    Summary:
    Pull Request resolved: https://github.com/facebookresearch/torcharrow/pull/190

    This diff refactors two things:

    1. Removes `genUnaryExprSet()`, `genCastExprSet()` and `applyUnaryExprSet()`. Replaces all of uses of those functions with `OperatorHandle::from*()` and `OperatorHandle::call()`.
    2. Refactors `SimpleColumn<T>::cast()` to use `OperatorHandle` so that it is easy to take the return type of the cast as a value parameter at runtime. This allows us to create an `OperatorHandle` on the fly, for each return type, which avoids the N^2 blow-up of cast functions.

    Reviewed By: wenleix, OswinC

